	"class": "vulnerability",
	"metadata": {
		"title": "golang.org/x/crypto/ssh: Misuse of ServerConfig.PublicKeyCallback may cause authorization bypass in golang.org/x/crypto (important)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2024-45337",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-45337",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A flaw was found in the x/crypto/ssh go library. Applications and libraries that misuse the ServerConfig.PublicKeyCallback callback may be susceptible to an authorization bypass. For example, an attacker may send public keys A and B and authenticate with A. PublicKeyCallback would be called only twice, first with A and then with B. A vulnerable application may then make authorization decisions based on key B, for which the attacker does not control the private key. The misuse of ServerConfig.PublicKeyCallback may cause an authorization bypass.",
